storyInfo: Gavial is away from the Island on an urgent mission, putting Tomimi down in the dumps. Fortunately, with a little help from her friends, she overcomes her negative feelings, and gradually adapts to life without Gavial at Rhodes Island.

attributes.content: Rhodes Island Landship
Dormitories, outside Gavial's room
Good morning, Gavial, it's time to get up.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (She's not here...)
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (That's really weird. Did Gavial wake up early today?)
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (Maybe she's eating breakfast already. I'll check the cafeteria.)
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (Gavial's not here either...)
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (She's not sleeping, and she's not here eating.)
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (She probably had something important to do today.)
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (I don't think she had any field missions coming up, so the only place she can be is Medical.)
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Whuh—huh?!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Wh—what's going on?!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: I only overheard it from my other colleagues.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: We had an emergency call last night from a nearby settlement. It's a complex situation.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: We had to send out an accompanying Operator with both combat and medical experience to ensure the other operators' safety.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: And out of the whole department, Gavial's the best fit for times like these.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: The mission really was urgent. Every Operator who took up the call for deployment headed out right away.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Why... what's...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: She probably left you something, right? A message, a slip of paper, the sort.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Let me look!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (Turns on comms terminal)
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: N—Nothing!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: But why...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (Ever since we left Acahualla, she—she's never come to say hello...)
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Gavial couldn't have... couldn't have abandoned me again, right?!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Er, you're overthinking it...
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: I'll go help her right now!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Wait, wait, wait, hold on! How are you gonna get there? Walk?
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: I... I'll drive over!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Settle down. You need to get permission from the motor pool, not to mention you don't know where you're going.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: And that's before we get to the part where you don't know how to drive.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: I—I could...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Uwh—wuhh...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: W-What are you crying for...?
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Oh, come on, quit it.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: *whimper*...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: I know you're worried for Gavial.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: But you oughta know. It's Gavial, what's to worry about?
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: No one could ever lay a finger on her.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: I'm scared she'll... get... get a graze...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: She's a Medic Operator. She can cure wounds like that herself just fine.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: But, what if she—
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Alright, alright, you weeping here isn't gonna solve anything, is it?
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Just go back and rest for a bit, settle your emotions, and do something to cheer yourself up, okay?
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: It was an urgent mission, but it's nothing tough. Give her, maybe, three, four days to her triumphant return.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Don't scare yourself.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: O—Okay...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: I'm sorry for being such a pain...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: No harm done, ha ha. Go on, head back and relax.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: I will...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: I didn't think going Gavialless would hit her so hard.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Must've left a deep impression on her when Gavial up left home the first time.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: I've gotta remind Gavial, you tell your loved ones before you go.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Or else we'll get a repeat of this. What if Tomimi cries the department six feet under water?
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Something that sad could happen?
Who knows?
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Take a seat, Blue Poison. Are you feeling unwell anywhere?
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Gavial...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Gavial's out on a mission...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: I want to go on a mission with Gavial too.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Do something to cheer myself up...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: What should I do? Is there anything I can do?
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: *Sigh*...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: If only I could be as strong as her...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Um...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Um?
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Where—am I?
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: I'm lost in Rhodes Island again. If Gavial finds out, she'll bonk me...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (Someone's over there. Maybe I can ask her.)
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Um. Hello?
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Hello, Archosauria. Is there anything I can assist you with?
attributes.name: Passerby Liberi

attributes.content: (Graceful curtsy)
attributes.name: Passerby Liberi

attributes.content: Wuh, uwh-wah.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (Imitates the curtsy)
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Hello, could I bother you to tell me where I am?
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: If you mean your specific position, we're in a corridor to the Rhodes Island hangar.
attributes.name: Passerby Liberi

attributes.content: Thank you, Miss Liberi!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Make no mention.
attributes.name: Passerby Liberi

attributes.content: You seem as though—you're a little bewildered. Do you need my help?
attributes.name: Passerby Liberi

attributes.content: I'm lost...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Ah, I see.
attributes.name: Passerby Liberi

attributes.content: Where did you lose your way?
attributes.name: Passerby Liberi

attributes.content: I'm sorry, I seem to have asked a silly question.
attributes.name: Passerby Liberi

attributes.content: Ahem—in that case, where do you want to go?
attributes.name: Passerby Liberi

attributes.content: I want... to buy a fashion magazine. I haven't read one in a long time, since leaving Acahualla. I'm feeling the itch.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: A magazine, hmm. I understand.
attributes.name: Passerby Liberi

attributes.content: If you want to buy magazines, take the elevator there up two floors, then turn right when you come out and go straight; after you see the little fountain, turn left, and you'll find a bookstand.
attributes.name: Passerby Liberi

attributes.content: The prices might be a little higher than in the city, but they have stable suppliers, a varied selection, and you can order in any publications you'd like.
attributes.name: Passerby Liberi

attributes.content: Alright. Thank you, I'll go take a look right now.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Just wait one moment.
attributes.name: Passerby Liberi

attributes.content: Before you leave, could I hassle you to assuage a small doubt of mine?
attributes.name: Passerby Liberi

attributes.content: Huh? Um, you can just ask, no need to be so polite.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Very good, I'll keep that in mind~
attributes.name: Passerby Liberi

attributes.content: Archosauria, does the burden on your shoulders weigh on you?
attributes.name: Passerby Liberi

attributes.content: Burden? You mean my backpack?
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (Weighs backpack in hand)
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: It's alright, it's not that heavy.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: It's all my specially selected treasures inside. I need to keep them close to me.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Can't you put them in your dormitory? That's your little slice of home at Rhodes Island.
attributes.name: Passerby Liberi

attributes.content: But I'd be really sad if I ever lost it.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: I can't let even one thing go missing. I'm better off keeping it with me.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Your recollections, your keepsakes, hmm...
attributes.name: Passerby Liberi

attributes.content: Have you ever thought of putting them in a safe?
attributes.name: Passerby Liberi

attributes.content: No, no way!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: My treasures will be angry if I lock them in a box!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Well, then, give your dormitory a proper furnishing, and turn it into your very own museum. Maybe that'd be nicer?
attributes.name: Passerby Liberi

attributes.content: Knowing to bear your recollections is a good thing, but perhaps in learning to unload burdens and adorn them, there's more significance still.
attributes.name: Passerby Liberi

attributes.content: Um, I don't really, get what you're saying.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: It's nothing. Just a solitary Liberi's meaningless soliloquy.
attributes.name: Passerby Liberi

attributes.content: My question has already found an answer. Thank you.
attributes.name: Passerby Liberi

attributes.content: Ah.
attributes.name: Passerby Liberi

attributes.content: Do you want me to guide you?
attributes.name: Passerby Liberi

attributes.content: No, it's okay, I think I can find my way! Thank you!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Then I'll bid farewell, Archosauria.
attributes.name: Passerby Liberi

attributes.content: Perhaps we'll meet again very soon.
attributes.name: Passerby Liberi

attributes.content: (Sargonian dialect) May your outlook be as boundless as the great forest.
attributes.name: Passerby Liberi

attributes.content: (Graceful curtsy)
attributes.name: Passerby Liberi

attributes.content: (She looks like she's really in a hurry.)
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (Is that Liberi at the other end her sister?)
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (They seem really close.)
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (That's so nice.)
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (I've reached the tiny fountain. Turn left...)
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: And this should be it.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Waah, Rhodes Island has stalls like this too?
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: It's your first time shopping at ours, isn't it?
attributes.name: Logistics Operator

attributes.content: The store's too cramped, and sometimes when we can't fit all our stock, the stall comes out. Of course, it's all approved and filed on record in advance. There's no shady business here.
attributes.name: Logistics Operator

attributes.content: What are you looking to buy?
attributes.name: Logistics Operator

attributes.content: I wanna buy the latest fashion magazine.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Fashion magazines come in many varieties. See, ones for getting into pendants and jewelry, ones putting out celebrity news, ones for announcing what's trendy in clothes, and—
attributes.name: Logistics Operator

attributes.content: Please give me the ones about clothes, thank you.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: This one's... all sold out on the latest issue.
attributes.name: Logistics Operator

attributes.content: Okay...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (I'm having the worst luck today...)
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: But you're in luck. The Operator who bought the last copy's still here. If you really want to read it, you could go ask her if she'd be willing to share with you.
attributes.name: Logistics Operator

attributes.content: Okay!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Which one is she?
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Over there, the one with pink hair.
attributes.name: Logistics Operator

attributes.content: She's called Blue Poison, and she's the first in to buy magazines every time. Seems she got held up today, and almost missed out.
attributes.name: Logistics Operator

attributes.content: Go give her a shout. She'll share with you, I think—
attributes.name: Logistics Operator

attributes.content: Alright, thank you!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Wait, I'm not done, she—
attributes.name: Logistics Operator

attributes.content: Whatever, sometimes less is more.
attributes.name: Logistics Operator

attributes.content: Maybe Blue Poison'll make a new friend this way.
attributes.name: Logistics Operator

attributes.content: H—Hello... would you happen to be Blue Poison? I'm Tomimi.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (So this is Tomimi? What a fine coincidence.)
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: (Holds out hand)
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: You want... to shake hands with—me?
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: Oh, I just thought, um, it's the polite thing to do and...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: If you don't want to, then—
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (Shakes Tomimi's hand)
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: I'm Blue Poison. I'm very happy to meet you.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: Because of... reasons... most people aren't too happy to—make contact—with me.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: So I was surprised when you held out your hand. Sorry for that.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: Did you need something from me?
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: I want to borrow your magazine to read a little, is that okay? I'll give it right back.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Magazine? You mean this issue of Me Maze?
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: Yes.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: I'm sorry, my Victorian isn't too good, so I can't read the words here so well.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: I only just picked it up, so I haven't read it yet.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: There's too many people around. Let's find somewhere to sit down and have a read at our own pace.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: Okay, I'll follow you.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Um.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: I'm done reading.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Thank you, Blue Poison.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Hm? Oh, no problem.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: Miss Tomimi.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: You can just call me Tomimi. Adding a title to a code name is a little weird...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Ah, alright, Tomimi.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: This morning... what happened?
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: An operator at Medical said you could've cried the whole department six feet under water.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: It's... kind of embarrassing to say.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: You'll feel better getting it out. Give it a try.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: Well, it's like this...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: That's the whole story, more or less.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Please don't laugh at me...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Of course I wouldn't.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: You know, I've heard that Archosauria never shed tears.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: Tears are a sign of weakness, so you can never, ever cry in front of anyone else.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: But even so, you'll still cry for Gavial.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: And there's nothing embarrassing about it at all.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: Ohh, thank you.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: I see you have an interest in clothing and fashion magazines. Does your homeland have such publications too?
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: No, but sometimes Inam would bring some from the outside for me.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: She's the one who does business in our place, so she always brings interesting stuff back. She taught me the outsiders' languages.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: After I learned them, I bought books from her to read, and I really liked the stuff in some of them, so I kind of ended up reading more.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Such as?
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: City Beauty and other ones like that.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Mm-hm, that was a fairly notable fashion magazine for sure.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: But... their works have been too streamlined, too cookie cutter. They've definitely lost a lot of their mystique... *sigh*...
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: I hear a few editors and photographers of theirs want to jump ship and set up their own shop. Who knows yet if that'll come to anything.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: You really, really know a lot about fashion, Blue Poison. You're incredible...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Not quite. I just read around, and have some of my own tastes and opinions, that's all.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: How about you, Tomimi? What is fashion to you?
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: I'm not too sure. My mother tongue doesn't have the vocabulary to talk fashion.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: It has plenty for hitting people, though.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Hahah...
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: I think, fashion is probably nice-looking clothes, and simple and pretty jewelry.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Acahualla doesn't have anything like that.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: The first time I opened that magazine was the first time I learned clothes could come in colors like that, and designs like that.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Some clothes I probably couldn't ever imagine in my life, but someday or other, they'd appear in the magazines Inam was selling, and I could say for sure—
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: —I really liked those clothes.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: There you go. I'd call you knowledgeable any day.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: Actually, the clothes I'm wearing right now are from when I saw some I really liked in a magazine, so I worked on making the whole outfit and adjusting it myself.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Although it's a little rough...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Ah, I think it's ringing a bell...
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: Hm...
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: (Opens and flips through her own personal notepad)
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: MARTHE... Mad Wild... Fury's Call... Swimming Suit series... Coral Coast...
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: Found it.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: Take a look. Was it this outfit?
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: Oh, it was!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: How do you know it?!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: It's in my collection. Sometimes, if I meet with a design I particularly like, I'll cut it out and stick it in this notepad, and then write my own gains from it.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: Y—You cut them out? Won't that ruin the magazine?
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: It's—how do I put it... I suppose it's a personal habit of mine.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: Cutting and pasting magazine pictures does spoil the print's intactness, but to me, it's a shortcut.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: Shortcut?
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Taking all the knowledge you want most from a magazine, and putting it in one place.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: And through that shortcut, it ends up in here.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: In your head?
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Mm-hm.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: This notepad I'm holding is my sixth one already.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: I only ever pull out the first few to flick through when I want to feel nostalgic.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: Inside them, save for memories, there's nothing left at all.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: The truly important things have all gone into my brain.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: They've become my aesthetics, tastes, styles.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: Can brains really remember that much?
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Of course not. What's left behind is only the parts you least want to forget.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: Such as, your choices and aspirations for beauty.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: Or maybe, in your case, um—
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: Gavial?
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: Oh, you're right. I definitely couldn't forget Gavial.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: The most important memories, they're always in your head.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: Sometimes, things are just keys for opening them up.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: Once you consolidate the memories and they're like an automatic door, you'll never need the key again.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: That... that makes sense.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Keys... treasure...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Memories...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Tomimi, have you ever tried styling outfits before?
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: Styling? No, not yet.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Then let's go to the shops and try on some clothes, what do you think?
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: Try them? Can—can I?!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Sure.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: Though the selection's not as complete as stores in the big cities, I can take you to experience it at least.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: If you don't mind, I can take us to visit a tailor, to get you even more style suggestions.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: I—is that—really something you can do?!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Of course. If you want, we can even have a whole outfit custom-made for you here at Rhodes Island.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: (Small mutter) Although the prices aren't too customer-friendly...
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: O—Okay, I, uh, I, I'll get ready.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: We're gonna try on clothes in a moment, right?
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Mhm.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: Then I—I, I need to put my backpack in my dorm first, and then it'll be less tricky when I'm trying them on.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: The fact you've gained awareness of this is something worth celebrating, you know.
attributes.name: Passerby Liberi

attributes.content: Ah, it's Miss Liberi from just before!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: I forgot to introduce myself previously. Do forgive me for my negligence.
attributes.name: Passerby Liberi

attributes.content: Astesia Urbica. Most usually call me just Astesia.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Pleased to make your acquaintance.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Hello, Miss Urbica.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (Holds out hand)
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (Elegantly shakes hands)
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Good afternoon, Miss Urbica.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: Good afternoon, Blue Poison.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: I want to take Tomimi to try on some clothes. If you could—
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: As luck has it, I want to pick out some new clothes for myself too. It would be my greatest pleasure to go with you.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: As for Bibeak, I wager she's still at the bookstand, buying the print.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Oh, my. It seems I wagered correctly.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: (You really can't get anything past her...)
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: I'll go give Bibeak a heads-up.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: See you in a bit.
attributes.name: Blue Poison

attributes.content: (Hushed) Astesia, Miss Urbica!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (Hushed) What's the matter?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: (Hushed) You said before, about furnishing into a museum. How do I really do that?
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (Hushed) Here. See that little water fountain?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: (Hushed) Mmhm.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (Hushed) There's a sculpted relief on top of it. Isn't it pretty?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: (Hushed) Mmhm.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (Hushed) If that fountain was your own meticulously preserved piece, would that make you feel, well, delighted?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: (Hushed) Um... mmhm!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (Hushed) And that's the way it works.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: (Hushed) Placing beautiful memories on pedestals specially made for them—it always has the power to cheer oneself up.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: (Hushed) If you need it, you can install further equipment on the pedestals too. You can protect things from outside damage, and greatly extend their lifetimes.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: (Hushed) That sounds pretty good.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (Hushed) Then, if, if you have time, could I ask you to, help me, um, plan it out?
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (Hushed) Of course.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: (Hushed) Choosing decor has its own particularities. When you're done trying on clothes, we can take our time with research.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: For now, we'll go meet up with Blue Poison and her friends. It would never do to keep them waiting.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Okay!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Tomimi.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: What is it, Miss Urbica?
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Do you feel in a better mood now?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Yes!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Doing what I like—makes me really happy.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Oh, that's wonderful.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Let's go, then.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Alright!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: The difference between Rhodes Island and Acahualla is kind of big.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: There's a lot you can't do here, and the rooms are pretty small.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: But I don't mind it that much.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: I can learn so many new things, and make new friends.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: There's nothing that makes me happier.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Maybe I can become a fashion expert, or an explorer, or a Caster.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Or maybe a fashionable Caster with an exploring spirit?
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: And what fun stuff might happen in the future?
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: I'm really looking forward to it.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: I guess when Gavial chose to stay at Rhodes Island, and not in Acahualla, this was why.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: I wonder what Gavial's up to now?
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Hold still! It'll just hurt for ONE moment.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Ow, gentle, you're killing me!
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: I said it'd hurt, not kill you.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Hm?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Hmph.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: All bound up. You put some pressure on that wound, and I'll give our guests a warm welcome.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Hah!
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Urgh...
Hey! What's with these punks creeping up here?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Sorry, Gavial! We only let that one guy slip, the others are all done and dusted!
attributes.name: Field Captain

attributes.content: Everyone, rest up where you are, and stay vigilant!
attributes.name: Field Captain

attributes.content: Understood!
attributes.name: All Field Operators

attributes.content: Phew. It's finally over.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Yep. Long as you're all alright.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Gavial.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Hm?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: You had real short notice for this mission. Did you ever send your hometown friend any regards?
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: What regards am I gonna give? I know her.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Not sure about anyone else, but the one who keeps coming to Medical, same race as you, right? You could at least give her a shout.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: What if she didn't find you, and cried Rhodes Island under water?
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Us Acahualla expats are all strongest of the strong. Tomimi sure as hell isn't that weak.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Besides, I ran some work with Astesia pretty recently. Anything happens, and she'll be there to help manage, guaranteed.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Fine, yeah, you got it all worked out already. Pretend I never asked.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Less yapping, more helping me figure the post-mission out. Where are we linking up with the R.I. landship?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Oh, yeah, one sec.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Um... here.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Landship'll be calling at this city for rest and resupply.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Hear it's a holiday city too. Giant coastal beach in there, wide open to tourists.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Thinking what I'm thinking? We can take a vacation.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Doesn't that work out.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: (Holiday city... coastal beach?)
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: (How about I buy her an outfit for the waterside? She oughta like that.)
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: (Yeah. Call it an apology.)
attributes.name: Gavial
